{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/UnevenRoundedRectangle"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/UnevenRoundedRectangle\/geometryGroup()"},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Isolates the geometry (e.g. position and size) of the view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from its parent view."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"geometryGroup","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default OpenSwiftUI views push position and size changes down"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"through the view hierarchy, so that only views that draw"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"something (known as leaf views) apply the current animation to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"their frame rectangle. However in some cases this coalescing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"behavior can give undesirable results; inserting a geometry"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"group can correct that. A group acts as a barrier between the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parent view and its subviews, forcing the position and size"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"values to be resolved and animated by the parent, before being"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"passed down to each subview."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The example below shows one use of this function: ensuring that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the member views of each row in the stack apply (and animate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as) a single geometric transform from their ancestor view,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"rather than letting the effects of the ancestor views be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"applied separately to each leaf view. If the members of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"ItemView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" may be added and removed at different times the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"group ensures that they stay locked together as animations are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"applied.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["VStack {","    ForEach(items) { item in","        ItemView(item: item)","            .geometryGroup()","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Returns: a new view whose geometry is isolated from that of its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parent view.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/unevenroundedrectangle\/geometrygroup()"]}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Method","externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewPAAE13geometryGroupQryF::SYNTHESIZED::s:15OpenSwiftUICore22UnevenRoundedRectangleV","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"geometryGroup","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"}],"title":"geometryGroup()","remoteSource":{"fileName":"RendererEffect.swift","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Render\/RendererEffect\/RendererEffect.swift#L304"},"modules":[{"relatedModules":["OpenSwiftUICore"],"name":"OpenSwiftUI"}],"symbolKind":"method","platforms":[{"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"13.0","name":"iOS","unavailable":false},{"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"10.15","name":"macOS","unavailable":false},{"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"13.0","name":"tvOS","unavailable":false},{"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"1.0","name":"visionOS","unavailable":false},{"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"6.0","name":"watchOS","unavailable":false}],"extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"sections":[],"references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/UnevenRoundedRectangle":{"url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/unevenroundedrectangle","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/UnevenRoundedRectangle","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnevenRoundedRectangle","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"UnevenRoundedRectangle","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"UnevenRoundedRectangle","abstract":[{"text":"A rectangular shape with rounded corners with different values, aligned","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"inside the frame of the view containing it.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/UnevenRoundedRectangle/geometryGroup()":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/UnevenRoundedRectangle\/geometryGroup()","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"geometryGroup"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"}],"title":"geometryGroup()","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Isolates the geometry (e.g. position and size) of the view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from its parent view."}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/unevenroundedrectangle\/geometrygroup()"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Declare the user interface and behavior for your app on every platform."}],"url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui","type":"topic","title":"OpenSwiftUI","role":"collection"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/View":{"url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/view","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"View","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","title":"View","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A type that represents part of your app’s user interface and provides"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"modifiers that you use to configure views."}],"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View"}}}